Terror<br><center><img src=http://EQbubbles.homestead.com/files/Charcothgl.jpg> <a/><center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=444444><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/usenaantruesilver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senaan Truesilver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seneschal<br>First Knight Champion</span><br>  Posts: 707<br> <font color=#FFFCCC>(4/18/02 11:15:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fknightsoffreedom94013frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=608.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sara and the powers od earth, water, and wind</span><hr size=1> If your serious about your epic, play nicely and help the guild out as much as you can. Then when the time comes, I know of someone that's willing to MQ their Pegasus Feathered Cloak to a Mage trying for their epic, if said mage was worthy. That way you won't have to compete against those silly level 20ish rangers and druids in Southern Karana.<br>
<br>
Anyhoo, congrats on the first few steps. The pet is worth it, but that path in getting the scepter is a bugger. Good luck and salute. <p>Senaan Truesilver<br>Seneschal of the Knights<br>Loving husband of Joslin<br><a target=new href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=97689>Lowbie_Gear</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=555555><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/ujoslintruesilver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Joslin Truesilver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The BIG Guy's BOSS</span><br>  Posts: 380<br> <font color=#FFFCCC>(4/18/02 11:20:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fknightsoffreedom94013frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=608.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sara and the powers od earth, water, and wind</span><hr size=1> Congrats!  I have had the chance to see the mage epic in use and all I can say is WOW!  I am not fimilar with what all you have to do to get the mage epic, but it has to be difficult.  An old friend of mine who has been level 60 for what seems like for ever now (and is also a member of SR) just got her epic recently.  Some of us grouped with her in Seb the other night and at that time her pet would solo a mob in about the same amount of time or quicker than Senaan, Mort, and myself could take one out.  I wish you the best of luck and let me know if there is anything I can do to help you with it.<br>
<br>
 <p>Joslin Truesilver<br>48th season Ranger of Tunare<br>and loving wife of Senaan<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82469">Joslin</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87401">Raiser (Necromancer)</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87410">Kekin (Warrior)</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87329">Viam (Monk)</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87415">Joslen (Cleric)</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=444444><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/urastalasilverymoon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rastala Silverymoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Squire</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FFFCCC>(4/18/02 12:09:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fknightsoffreedom94013frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=608.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sara and the powers od earth, water, and wind</span><hr size=1> Thanks all for the kind responses.  Yes im serious about getting my epic.  let me say HOLY WOW!!  That is super amazing that the epic pet can solo better than the 3 of you hehe.  That would totally rock.  I am up for helping anyone with their epics as I know they suck doing.  I think the CoM thing is something we should start hitting once or twice a week.  We got the muscle to do it I think and alot of us need items from there.  It would be cool to go and get em.  However on planar items its going to be hit and miss with me as I am about to change schedules at work and most likely will only be able to make raids at wierd times as they take so darned long.  But yes im very very serious about getting my epic.  Sat 11 hours in sola to get my power of fire.  But by God I got it. <br>
